time. On the hardness side, we prove that\nevaluating $Z(\\mathbf{z})$ at an arbitrary point in Shearer's region, and\ntesting membership in Shearer's region, are #P-hard problems. We also establish\nthe best possible dependence of the exponent of the run time of Weitz's\ncorrelation decay technique in the negative regime on the distance to the\nboundary of the Shearer region.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 7 Aug 2016 23:49:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 11 Nov 2017 20:46:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-11-15"}
